This paper deals with the problem of enabling robots to express their incapability in a way that communicates both what they are trying to accomplish and why they are unable to accomplish it. This involves trajectory optimization and similarity measures, which are common topics in robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the effectiveness of the approach through a user study, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision techniques to analyze the robot's motion, which could fall under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Overall, cs.RO and cs.AI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.HC, cs.LG (machine learning), and cs.CV.
